provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html — Python asyncio module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Modules/_asynciomodule.c"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends asyncio_extra99.zspec.zsdl."
    - "This spec covers: wave 254 theme — asyncio module __spec__, __package__, __name__ attrs and key submodule names. NEW in extra102: asyncio.__name__=='asyncio' (len=7); asyncio.__package__=='asyncio' (package name equals module name); asyncio.__spec__.__class__.__name__=='ModuleSpec'; asyncio.__spec__.name=='asyncio'; asyncio.__spec__.submodule_search_locations.__class__.__name__=='list' (asyncio is a package with submodule search paths); asyncio.__spec__.has_location==True; asyncio.__file__.__class__.__name__=='str'; asyncio.tasks.__name__=='asyncio.tasks' (len=13); asyncio.locks.__name__=='asyncio.locks' (len=13, tied with tasks); asyncio.queues.__name__=='asyncio.queues' (len=14); asyncio.events.__name__=='asyncio.events' (len=14, tied with queues); asyncio.streams.__name__=='asyncio.streams' (len=15); asyncio.runners.__name__=='asyncio.runners' (len=15, tied with streams); asyncio.protocols.__name__=='asyncio.protocols' (len=17). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.__name__.__len__() == 7. 'asyncio' is 7 characters: a-s-y-n-c-i-o. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.__spec__.submodule_search_locations.__class__.__name__ == 'list'. asyncio is a package (directory-based module with __init__.py); its submodule_search_locations is a plain list containing the package directory path. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.__package__ == asyncio.__name__ == 'asyncio'. For top-level packages, __package__ equals __name__; this contrasts with submodules like asyncio.tasks where __package__ != __name__. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

